{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015MHzmogaSfHzDLZMW5fAhn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/usr/bin/env bash\n     2→# retry.sh — ClawClau v2: Retry a failed task with an improved prompt\n     3→#\n     4→# Usage: retry.sh <task-id> [\"<improved prompt>\"]\n     5→#\n     6→# If no improved prompt is given, the original prompt is reused with a failure\n     7→# context block prepended.\n     8→#\n     9→# Retry task IDs follow the pattern: <original-id>-retry-<n>\n    10→\n    11→set -euo pipefail\n    12→SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")\" && pwd)\"\n    13→source \"$SCRIPT_DIR/lib.sh\"\n    14→\n    15→cc_require tmux jq\n    16→\n    17→if [[ $# -lt 1 ]]; then\n    18→    echo \"Usage: retry.sh <task-id> [\\\"<improved prompt>\\\"]\" >&2; exit 1\n    19→fi\n    20→\n    21→TASK_ID=\"$1\"\n    22→NEW_PROMPT=\"${2:-}\"\n    23→\n    24→if ! cc_task_exists \"$TASK_ID\"; then\n    25→    echo \"ERROR: task '$TASK_ID' not found in registry\" >&2; exit 1\n    26→fi\n    27→\n    28→# Check task is not running\n    29→SESSION=$(cc_tmux_session \"$TASK_ID\")\n    30→if tmux has-session -t \"$SESSION\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    31→    echo \"ERROR: task '$TASK_ID' is still running. Kill it first with kill.sh.\" >&2; exit 1\n    32→fi\n    33→\n    34→# Read task metadata\n    35→STATUS=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"status\")\n    36→RETRY_COUNT=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"retryCount\")\n    37→MAX_RETRIES=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"maxRetries\")\n    38→ORIGINAL_PROMPT=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"prompt\")\n    39→LOG_FILE=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"log\")\n    40→WORKDIR=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"workdir\")\n    41→AGENT=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"agent\")\n    42→MODE=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"mode\")\n    43→WORKTREE=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"worktree\")\n    44→BRANCH=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"branch\")\n    45→DONE_CHECK=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"doneCheck\")\n    46→MODEL=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"model\")\n    47→\n    48→# Enforce retry limit\n    49→RETRY_COUNT=\"${RETRY_COUNT:-0}\"\n    50→MAX_RETRIES=\"${MAX_RETRIES:-3}\"\n    51→if [[ \"$RETRY_COUNT\" -ge \"$MAX_RETRIES\" ]]; then\n    52→    echo \"ERROR: task '$TASK_ID' has reached max retries ($MAX_RETRIES/$MAX_RETRIES)\" >&2\n    53→    echo \"  To override, create a new task manually with spawn.sh\" >&2\n    54→    exit 1\n    55→fi\n    56→\n    57→# Build the new task ID\n    58→NEW_RETRY_COUNT=$((RETRY_COUNT + 1))\n    59→NEW_TASK_ID=\"${TASK_ID}-retry-${NEW_RETRY_COUNT}\"\n    60→\n    61→# Build the improved prompt\n    62→if [[ -z \"$NEW_PROMPT\" ]]; then\n    63→    # No custom prompt given — prepend failure context to original\n    64→    FAILURE_SNIPPET=\"\"\n    65→    if [[ -f \"$LOG_FILE\" ]] && [[ -s \"$LOG_FILE\" ]]; then\n    66→        FAILURE_SNIPPET=$(cc_extract_text \"$LOG_FILE\" 300)\n    67→    fi\n    68→\n    69→    STEER_HISTORY=$(jq -r --arg id \"$TASK_ID\" \\\n    70→        '.[] | select(.id == $id) | .steerLog[] | \"- [\\(.at)] \\(.message)\"' \\\n    71→        \"$CC_REGISTRY\" 2>/dev/null || true)\n    72→\n    73→    CONTEXT_BLOCK=\"[Retry $NEW_RETRY_COUNT/$MAX_RETRIES — Previous attempt '$TASK_ID' failed]\"\n    74→    [[ -n \"$FAILURE_SNIPPET\" ]] && CONTEXT_BLOCK+=$'\\n'\"Last output: $FAILURE_SNIPPET\"\n    75→    [[ -n \"$STEER_HISTORY\" ]] && CONTEXT_BLOCK+=$'\\n'\"Steer history:\"$'\\n'\"$STEER_HISTORY\"\n    76→    CONTEXT_BLOCK+=$'\\n'\"Please retry carefully addressing the above issues.\"$'\\n'\n    77→\n    78→    NEW_PROMPT=\"${CONTEXT_BLOCK}\"$'\\n'\"${ORIGINAL_PROMPT}\"\n    79→else\n    80→    # Custom prompt given — just prepend minimal context\n    81→    NEW_PROMPT=\"[Retry $NEW_RETRY_COUNT/$MAX_RETRIES of task '$TASK_ID']\"$'\\n'\"${NEW_PROMPT}\"\n    82→fi\n    83→\n    84→# Update parent task status to retrying\n    85→cc_task_update \"$TASK_ID\" \"{\\\"status\\\":\\\"retrying\\\"}\"\n    86→\n    87→echo \"Retrying: $TASK_ID → $NEW_TASK_ID (retry $NEW_RETRY_COUNT/$MAX_RETRIES)\"\n    88→echo \"\"\n    89→\n    90→# Build spawn.sh arguments\n    91→SPAWN_ARGS=(\n    92→    --agent \"$AGENT\"\n    93→    --timeout \"$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"timeout\")\"\n    94→    --max-retries \"$MAX_RETRIES\"\n    95→    --retry-count \"$NEW_RETRY_COUNT\"\n    96→    --parent \"$TASK_ID\"\n    97→)\n    98→\n    99→[[ \"$MODE\" == \"steerable\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--steerable)\n   100→[[ -n \"$WORKTREE\" ]] && [[ \"$WORKTREE\" != \"null\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--worktree)\n   101→[[ -n \"$BRANCH\" ]] && [[ \"$BRANCH\" != \"null\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--branch \"$BRANCH\")\n   102→[[ -n \"$DONE_CHECK\" ]] && [[ \"$DONE_CHECK\" != \"null\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--done-check \"$DONE_CHECK\")\n   103→[[ -n \"$MODEL\" ]] && [[ \"$MODEL\" != \"null\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--model \"$MODEL\")\n   104→\n   105→INTERVAL=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"interval\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n   106→[[ -n \"$INTERVAL\" ]] && [[ \"$INTERVAL\" != \"null\" ]] && [[ \"$INTERVAL\" -gt 0 ]] && \\\n   107→    SPAWN_ARGS+=(--interval \"$INTERVAL\")\n   108→\n   109→exec \"$SCRIPT_DIR/spawn.sh\" \"${SPAWN_ARGS[@]}\" \"$NEW_TASK_ID\" \"$NEW_PROMPT\" \"$WORKDIR\"\n   110→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"493fb87d-5bdf-4877-a927-bd41d6d235b6","uuid":"4c2aa99a-09fc-4a85-b84c-bd8ff00edb8f","timestamp":"2026-03-19T10:44:36.987Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/yjj/.openclaw/workspace/memory/clawclau2/retry.sh","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# retry.sh — ClawClau v2: Retry a failed task with an improved prompt\n#\n# Usage: retry.sh <task-id> [\"<improved prompt>\"]\n#\n# If no improved prompt is given, the original prompt is reused with a failure\n# context block prepended.\n#\n# Retry task IDs follow the pattern: <original-id>-retry-<n>\n\nset -euo pipefail\nSCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")\" && pwd)\"\nsource \"$SCRIPT_DIR/lib.sh\"\n\ncc_require tmux jq\n\nif [[ $# -lt 1 ]]; then\n    echo \"Usage: retry.sh <task-id> [\\\"<improved prompt>\\\"]\" >&2; exit 1\nfi\n\nTASK_ID=\"$1\"\nNEW_PROMPT=\"${2:-}\"\n\nif ! cc_task_exists \"$TASK_ID\"; then\n    echo \"ERROR: task '$TASK_ID' not found in registry\" >&2; exit 1\nfi\n\n# Check task is not running\nSESSION=$(cc_tmux_session \"$TASK_ID\")\nif tmux has-session -t \"$SESSION\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: task '$TASK_ID' is still running. Kill it first with kill.sh.\" >&2; exit 1\nfi\n\n# Read task metadata\nSTATUS=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"status\")\nRETRY_COUNT=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"retryCount\")\nMAX_RETRIES=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"maxRetries\")\nORIGINAL_PROMPT=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"prompt\")\nLOG_FILE=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"log\")\nWORKDIR=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"workdir\")\nAGENT=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"agent\")\nMODE=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"mode\")\nWORKTREE=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"worktree\")\nBRANCH=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"branch\")\nDONE_CHECK=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"doneCheck\")\nMODEL=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"model\")\n\n# Enforce retry limit\nRETRY_COUNT=\"${RETRY_COUNT:-0}\"\nMAX_RETRIES=\"${MAX_RETRIES:-3}\"\nif [[ \"$RETRY_COUNT\" -ge \"$MAX_RETRIES\" ]]; then\n    echo \"ERROR: task '$TASK_ID' has reached max retries ($MAX_RETRIES/$MAX_RETRIES)\" >&2\n    echo \"  To override, create a new task manually with spawn.sh\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Build the new task ID\nNEW_RETRY_COUNT=$((RETRY_COUNT + 1))\nNEW_TASK_ID=\"${TASK_ID}-retry-${NEW_RETRY_COUNT}\"\n\n# Build the improved prompt\nif [[ -z \"$NEW_PROMPT\" ]]; then\n    # No custom prompt given — prepend failure context to original\n    FAILURE_SNIPPET=\"\"\n    if [[ -f \"$LOG_FILE\" ]] && [[ -s \"$LOG_FILE\" ]]; then\n        FAILURE_SNIPPET=$(cc_extract_text \"$LOG_FILE\" 300)\n    fi\n\n    STEER_HISTORY=$(jq -r --arg id \"$TASK_ID\" \\\n        '.[] | select(.id == $id) | .steerLog[] | \"- [\\(.at)] \\(.message)\"' \\\n        \"$CC_REGISTRY\" 2>/dev/null || true)\n\n    CONTEXT_BLOCK=\"[Retry $NEW_RETRY_COUNT/$MAX_RETRIES — Previous attempt '$TASK_ID' failed]\"\n    [[ -n \"$FAILURE_SNIPPET\" ]] && CONTEXT_BLOCK+=$'\\n'\"Last output: $FAILURE_SNIPPET\"\n    [[ -n \"$STEER_HISTORY\" ]] && CONTEXT_BLOCK+=$'\\n'\"Steer history:\"$'\\n'\"$STEER_HISTORY\"\n    CONTEXT_BLOCK+=$'\\n'\"Please retry carefully addressing the above issues.\"$'\\n'\n\n    NEW_PROMPT=\"${CONTEXT_BLOCK}\"$'\\n'\"${ORIGINAL_PROMPT}\"\nelse\n    # Custom prompt given — just prepend minimal context\n    NEW_PROMPT=\"[Retry $NEW_RETRY_COUNT/$MAX_RETRIES of task '$TASK_ID']\"$'\\n'\"${NEW_PROMPT}\"\nfi\n\n# Update parent task status to retrying\ncc_task_update \"$TASK_ID\" \"{\\\"status\\\":\\\"retrying\\\"}\"\n\necho \"Retrying: $TASK_ID → $NEW_TASK_ID (retry $NEW_RETRY_COUNT/$MAX_RETRIES)\"\necho \"\"\n\n# Build spawn.sh arguments\nSPAWN_ARGS=(\n    --agent \"$AGENT\"\n    --timeout \"$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"timeout\")\"\n    --max-retries \"$MAX_RETRIES\"\n    --retry-count \"$NEW_RETRY_COUNT\"\n    --parent \"$TASK_ID\"\n)\n\n[[ \"$MODE\" == \"steerable\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--steerable)\n[[ -n \"$WORKTREE\" ]] && [[ \"$WORKTREE\" != \"null\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--worktree)\n[[ -n \"$BRANCH\" ]] && [[ \"$BRANCH\" != \"null\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--branch \"$BRANCH\")\n[[ -n \"$DONE_CHECK\" ]] && [[ \"$DONE_CHECK\" != \"null\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--done-check \"$DONE_CHECK\")\n[[ -n \"$MODEL\" ]] && [[ \"$MODEL\" != \"null\" ]] && SPAWN_ARGS+=(--model \"$MODEL\")\n\nINTERVAL=$(cc_task_get \"$TASK_ID\" \"interval\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n[[ -n \"$INTERVAL\" ]] && [[ \"$INTERVAL\" != \"null\" ]] && [[ \"$INTERVAL\" -gt 0 ]] && \\\n    SPAWN_ARGS+=(--interval \"$INTERVAL\")\n\nexec \"$SCRIPT_DIR/spawn.sh\" \"${SPAWN_ARGS[@]}\" \"$NEW_TASK_ID\" \"$NEW_PROMPT\" \"$WORKDIR\"\n","numLines":110,"startLine":1,"totalLines":110}}}
